    "extras": [
      "May through September is the sweet spot: long days, easy bus schedules and the best odds for clear fortress and Rugova views.",
      "Kosovo uses the euro, but local buses and short taxi hops are among the cheapest in the Balkans, so carrying small cash notes helps a lot.",
      "Dress modestly at Gračanica Monastery and the Patriarchate of Peć, and avoid arriving right in the middle of liturgy or monastery quiet hours.",
      "If you only have 3 to 4 days, keep Pristina and Prizren as the anchors and treat Peja or Gjakova as a single-night detour.",
      "English is common in tourism spots, but bus stations still run best with screenshots, small cash and a little timing flexibility."
    ],
